OL,7,FBut at 2am, the night before she was
OL,8,Fdue to fly, Sue received a phone call
OL,9,Ffrom Bethany and one of the hospital
OL,10,Fdoctors, asking her to give permission
OL,11,Ffor Simone to have urgent brain
OL,12,Fsurgery.
OL,14,F"As soon as they said brain surgery, I
OL,15,Fjust knew she wasn't going to make it.
OL,16,FLike mother's intuition, I just knew."
OL,18,FSue then had to endure the 17-hour
OL,19,Fplane journey to Laos alone, not
OL,20,Fknowing whether her daughter was alive
OL,21,For dead.
